It looks like the permission wasn't granted for the settings file write. Here's exactly what I was going to add to `~/.claude/settings.json`:

```json
"hooks": {
  "Stop": [
    {
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "([ -f package.json ] && npm run typecheck --if-present 2>&1) || true",
          "timeout": 120,
          "statusMessage": "Running typecheck..."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

This uses the `Stop` event — fires every time Claude finishes responding, so typecheck runs automatically after every coding session. The guard `[ -f package.json ]` means it silently skips in directories without a project. The `--if-present` flag skips silently if the `typecheck` script isn't defined.

If you'd like to proceed, approve the file write and I'll apply it. Or if you'd prefer a different scope (e.g. project-level `.claude/settings.json` instead of global), let me know.
